review.prompt:
Current task or question:
{{ inputs.task }}

Claude's latest response:
{{ inputs.claude_response }}

Additional context, if any:
{{ inputs.context }}

What do you think? Do not agree for the sake of agreeing, do not assume everything is true before deeply verifying (and writing/running tests when applicable). If relevant, inspect files and run non-mutating checks. Don't implement - just advise. Draw on prior context from this advisor thread when relevant, but do not rely on memory over evidence. Return: (1) Verdict: proceed / revise / block. (2) Concrete findings, ordered by severity, with file:line where applicable. (3) What Claude must verify before executing. (4) If there are no issues, say so plainly and name the remaining risk.
